com.rcextract.minecord.sql

Class SQLObjectConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rcextract.minecord.sql.SQLObjectConverter

  • public class SQLObjectConverter
extends Object
    An advanced converter class which provides utility methods for saving objects to the desired database and loading objects from it without using the "CREATE TYPE".

    The reason why "CREATE TYPE" is not implemented, is that firstly, not all SQL servers support this feature, and secondly, SQL is not made for us to save data like that. Columns should represent fields in a class in Java, and rows should represent objects of that class. Therefore, a converter is built for programmers to save Java objects without rewriting what is here.

    This converter also supports Java object referencing. For example, when both object A and object B stores the same object C before saving, it will still be the same after saving and loading. This system applies to all objects saved, except for numbers and booleans, because they will always return true when compared with == while returning true when compared with Object.equals(Object).

    Besides, this converter does not serialize an Object storing elements into a complex string. Instead, it will make a string storing the objects being referenced by the object, and save them if not done. This mechanics currently applies interally to ArrayList, HashMap, SQLList, and ArrayMap.

    It is strongly recommended to put an SQLList into the map returning from the DatabaseSerializable.serialize() than ArrayList, so the converter can get the element type most safely.
